- "treasure chest" represents the gold holdings of a player;
- "inventory" refers to the items a player possesses, each with a cost and quantity;
- "outshines even the average hoard of all adventurers" means the player's gold is greater than the average gold of all players;
- "stands tallest among the wealthy" implies the character with the highest total value of items in their inventory.

- 'Crafting items' refers to items that can be used to create new items in the game;
- 'Not equipped' means the items are in the inventory but not currently in use by the player;
- 'Enough quantity to meet the crafting requirements' means the quantity in the inventory is greater than the required quantity for crafting.

sql:
SELECT AVG(weight) AS average_weight
FROM items
WHERE category = 'Healing' AND weight > (SELECT AVG(weight) FROM items WHERE category = 'Healing');

